{"id":1044,"parent_id":0,"book_id":8,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":1044,"title":"Rimmon","subtitle":"","short_title":"Rimmon","uri":"/scriptures/bd/rimmon","content":[["div",{"id":"t1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/rimmon.t1","order":".000.3465"},[".title","Rimmon"],["div",{"id":"p1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/rimmon.p1","order":".000.3466"},"(1) God of the Syrians of Damascus (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/2-kgs/5.18"},"2 Kgs. 5:18"],"), identified by them with the sun god Hadad (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/zech/12.11"},"Zech. 12:11"],"). Among the Babylonians he was the god of the air, wind, thunder, and rain."],["div",{"id":"p2","uri":"/scriptures/bd/rimmon.p2","order":".000.3467"},"(2)",["i","Pomegranate."],"A Beerothite, father of Baanah and Rechab, the murderers of Ishbosheth (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/2-sam/4.2,5,9"},"2 Sam. 4:2, 5, 9"],")."],["div",{"id":"p3","uri":"/scriptures/bd/rimmon.p3","order":".000.3468"},"(3) A place in Judah in the Negev (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/josh/15.32"},"Josh. 15:32"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-chr/4.32"},"1 Chr. 4:32"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/zech/14.10"},"Zech. 14:10"],")."],["div",{"id":"p4","uri":"/scriptures/bd/rimmon.p4","order":".000.3469"},"(4) The rock Rimmon, in the wilderness of Benjamin, about 3½ miles east of Bethel (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/judg/20.45,47"},"Judg. 20:45, 47"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/judg/21.13"},"21:13"],")."]]],"refs":null}
